1
00:00:00,041 --> 00:00:01,042
Allie?

2
00:00:01,501 --> 00:00:02,335
Kara?

3
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:05,004
[JESS] I’m not Allie.

4
00:00:05,046 --> 00:00:06,047
Who are you?

5
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:09,175
Sorry, Jess. He thinks you’re his ex.

6
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:11,386
Sorry. I thought you were someone else.

7
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:12,637
Are you following me?

8
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:15,223
[JAO] Maybe we can rent a private boat.

9
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,932
You just won’t quit, huh?

10
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,309
I don’t give up easily.

11
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:21,019
[JAO] It's one of the qualities Allie liked about me.

12
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:21,730
[HAN BIN] Jao!

13
00:00:21,731 --> 00:00:24,524
This is Quinito, best chef in Manila.

14
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:25,733
And this is Jao.

15
00:00:25,734 --> 00:00:26,817
- Hi. Jao. - ‘Sup, brother?

16
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:27,485
Nice to meet you.

17
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:28,111
- Join us. - Come on, join.

18
00:00:28,112 --> 00:00:29,237
- Yeah! Karaoke night. - Karaoke night.

19
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:29,988
No, I’ll pass.

20
00:00:29,989 --> 00:00:31,656
I need to rest. I had a long day.

21
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:32,407
You guys enjoy.

22
00:00:32,408 --> 00:00:34,533
[SIARGAONON] Good evening to you all,

23
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:35,493
my Katig people!

24
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:38,121
[CROWD CHEERING]

25
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:39,496
[ARIEL] Han Bin oppa!

26
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:41,750
I didn’t know you had such a good singing voice.

27
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:42,751
- Thank you. - I’ll upload the video

28
00:00:42,752 --> 00:00:44,419
of your performance on my vlog, okay?

29
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:45,462
Please don’t do that.

30
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:46,504
Delete the video.

31
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,298
[HORN BLARING]

32
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:49,132
[KARA] Allie!

33
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:50,008
[ALLIE] Kara!

34
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:51,508
Oh, my gosh!

35
00:00:51,509 --> 00:00:53,678
Are you really set on that already?

36
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:56,514
I feel like Jao really cares for you a lot.

37
00:00:57,098 --> 00:01:00,560
[MIKA] Sir, I found this photo on one of Allie's friend’s profiles.

38
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:02,479
Taken just last month.

39
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:08,234
[HORN BLARING]

40
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:17,911
I’m sorry.

41
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:32,842
[MAN] Watch your step.

42
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:57,450
[ALON BY JL]

43
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:23,119
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

44
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:27,916
Jao?

45
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:45,641
Jao, I can explain.

46
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:46,726
You know Allie?

47
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:53,358
Why are you keeping her from me, Kara?

48
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,946
[KARA] Sorry, Jao…

49
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,948
she doesn’t want to see you.

50
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:02,241
I want to talk to her.

51
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:06,287
[KARA] She’s gone. She just left the island.

52
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:07,622
Take me to her.

53
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,292
Take me to her, Kara, please!

54
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:16,089
[KARA] Sorry, I don’t know where she went.

55
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,842
Do you think I still believe you?

56
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:24,180
All this time,

57
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:28,142
you were fooling me all along.

58
00:04:29,018 --> 00:04:32,105
All this time, you made me believe you didn't know Allie.

59
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:37,819
I didn’t mean to hurt you.

60
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:41,656
Allie is my friend, so I wanted to help her.

61
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:45,742
And I thought by keeping you away,

62
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:46,869
I was doing the right thing.

63
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:47,912
But I was wrong.

64
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:55,294
I convinced her to stay, but she really doesn't want to.

65
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,216
I want to talk to her.

66
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,218
I want to see her.

67
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:04,554
Please.

68
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:06,723
[KARA] I don’t know where she is.

69
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:07,890
Then call her!

70
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,936
I’m sure you have her new number.

71
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:15,023
She’s not picking up my calls.

72
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:16,733
Call her, please.

73
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:35,543
Please give me the sweet ones.

74
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:36,461
Yes.

75
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:37,837
Not that one.

76
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:39,672
Just three.

77
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:41,132
There you go.

78
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:42,675
- Allie. - Oh.

79
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:43,967
- Hello. - Hi.

80
00:05:43,968 --> 00:05:45,886
- [PHONE RINGING] - Wait.

81
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:48,222
[PHONE RINGING]

82
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:49,724
- It’s Kara. - Okay.

83
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:50,933
Hello, Kara?

84
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,351
[KARA] Hello, Allie?

85
00:05:53,811 --> 00:05:54,479
Allie?

86
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:56,606
Hello, Allie?

87
00:05:57,231 --> 00:05:58,232
Jao?

88
00:05:58,524 --> 00:05:59,525
[JAO] Uh…

89
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:01,611
Can we talk, please?

90
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:03,613
Uh…

91
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:05,531
Sorry if…

92
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:08,159
I did something to make you do this, but…

93
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:09,702
can we talk?

94
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,287
[JAO] Let’s fix this? Please, Allie?

95
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,372
Jao...

96
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:15,166
No.

97
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:18,336
[ALLIE] We can’t fix this.

98
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:19,754
Uh…

99
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,510
I think it’s time for you to let go.

100
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:28,679
Um…

101
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:33,726
It's not that easy...

102
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:39,524
Fifteen years, Allie.

103
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:43,569
[JAO] But…

104
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:46,614
Okay…

105
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:50,660
I understand.

106
00:06:50,661 --> 00:06:52,453
I understand if that's what you want.

107
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:54,247
But…

108
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:56,916
can we at least…

109
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,669
[JAO] see each other one last time?

110
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,088
Please?

111
00:07:08,469 --> 00:07:09,512
I’ll wait for you.

112
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:15,226
[BUSY TONE]

113
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:16,978
Well?

114
00:07:16,979 --> 00:07:18,354
[SIARGAONON] Did he find you?

115
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:46,048
Jao.

116
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:48,843
I’m really sorry.

117
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,805
I didn’t mean to hurt you.

118
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:56,184
I really was just protecting Allie.

119
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:09,322
I know Allie and I can still work this out.

120
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:13,075
We can fix this.

121
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:18,039
Where can I possibly meet her?

122
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:23,461
At the Dapa Pier?

123
00:08:44,982 --> 00:08:46,901
[CAROL] He didn’t get mad at you?

124
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:48,694
No.

125
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:51,030
How nice of him.

126
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:53,991
All he was really thinking about was Allie.

127
00:08:54,283 --> 00:08:55,952
Oh, Allie.

128
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:59,205
If she’d just talked to him, this would’ve been over by now.

129
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,668
I wonder how Jao is doing.

130
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:08,547
Seems like Kara is really concerned about Jao.

131
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:09,090
Right, Mom?

132
00:09:09,131 --> 00:09:10,007
Sure she does!

133
00:09:10,424 --> 00:09:12,551
How could I not be?

134
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:15,346
It’s partly my fault things got this bad.

135
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,598
I enabled Allie.

136
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:19,016
You did!

137
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,977
You should have minded your own business.

138
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,477
[SIARGAONON] Exactly.

139
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:23,312
[KARA SIGHS]

140
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,730
[KARA] No need to rub it in.

141
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:28,066
I wonder how I can make it up to him.

142
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,444
I want to iron things out.

143
00:09:30,486 --> 00:09:32,488
I want a clear conscience.

144
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:35,574
[ARIEL] Kara, do you think

145
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:37,618
Allie will meet up with Jao?

146
00:09:41,872 --> 00:09:43,457
At least this one’s ironed out.

147
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,925
[PAUL] How’s the Cebu project coming along?

148
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,428
I checked out the preliminary renders of the villas.

149
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:57,680
They look really good. Nice work.

150
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:00,181
Sir Darwin liked the presentation.

151
00:10:00,182 --> 00:10:02,685
The barefoot-luxury vibe is spot on.

152
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:04,687
Jao?

153
00:10:04,688 --> 00:10:06,272
- Sir! - Everything all right on your end?

154
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:06,939
Um…

155
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:07,565
[JAO CLEARS THROAT]

156
00:10:07,606 --> 00:10:09,024
Yes, sir, about the project…

157
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:11,569
we are closely coordinating with marketing

158
00:10:11,610 --> 00:10:13,571
so that they stay aligned with our design.

159
00:10:13,612 --> 00:10:14,989
[PAUL] When are you visiting the site?

160
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,533
We need boots on the ground to keep this thing tight.

161
00:10:18,075 --> 00:10:20,161
I’m thinking next week is perfect.

162
00:10:20,202 --> 00:10:22,454
I’m flying out Thursday, sir,

163
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:26,334
and probably would stay on site for at least three days.

164
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,168
[PAUL] Good.

165
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:28,753
Three days should be good enough

166
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:30,212
to get a solid grasp.

167
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:31,589
Keep me posted, okay?

168
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,799
This project’s going to be huge!

169
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:35,676
We can’t afford any slip-ups.

170
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,303
By the way, Jao…

171
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:40,306
We better start thinking about your next big project.

172
00:10:40,514 --> 00:10:42,641
I’m talking about something bigger than this.

173
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:43,767
That way,

174
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:45,811
I can recommend you to take over my position

175
00:10:45,853 --> 00:10:46,979
as Department Head.

176
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:48,898
So, do your best, okay?

177
00:10:48,939 --> 00:10:50,691
- I'm counting on you, Jao. - Got it, sir.

178
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:52,109
Don’t let me down.

179
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,161
[JAO] I’ll wait for you.

180
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:26,394
[HAN BIN HUMMING]

181
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:29,313
[PEARL] Oh!

182
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:33,025
What happened, Pearl?

183
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:34,527
Nothing, sir!

184
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:36,570
- Just got something in my eye... - Wait, let me see.

185
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:41,033
- Don’t move, okay? - Okay.

186
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,716
Smells like peppermint.

187
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,051
What?

188
00:11:59,718 --> 00:12:03,596
[STAMMERING]

189
00:12:03,597 --> 00:12:05,599
I said I’m preparing to walk.

190
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:08,017
Let’s go, sir. We might get late.

191
00:12:08,018 --> 00:12:09,019
Okay.

192
00:12:21,198 --> 00:12:22,867
Pearl, l’ve got this.

193
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,076
Thank you.

194
00:12:24,869 --> 00:12:25,786
Wanna sit together?

195
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:26,954
Sure!

196
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:29,790
Pearl! Sit in front.

197
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:30,833
Come with me.

198
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,668
What? Why?

199
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:35,421
I thought you knew the way to Pacifico already.

200
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:38,507
I get confused sometimes.

201
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:39,675
I need your help.

202
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,177
Okay.

203
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:41,927
Jao!

204
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:43,762
We are going to Pacifico. You wanna surf?

205
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,972
No, maybe next time. I need to go somewhere.

206
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:47,975
Too bad. You have a tour again?

207
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:50,728
No, actually, I found her, Mr. Han.

208
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:51,854
Oh!

209
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:52,855
I found Allie.

210
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:54,398
Oh!

211
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:55,524
OMG.

212
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,984
I’ll go ahead. Sorry!

213
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,777
- Very good nice! - Oh my gosh.

214
00:12:58,819 --> 00:12:59,737
Go on!

215
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:01,113
Let’s go.

216
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:31,644
[SIARGAONON] Kara, tell your friend to go home.

217
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:33,896
Poor guy’s been out there for hours.

218
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:23,696
[KARA] You good?

219
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,820
It’s really over, huh?

220
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:11,952
This is how it ends.

221
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:17,583
This is where our story ends.

222
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:50,616
It’s time to go, Jao.

223
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:55,204
[JAO SIGHS]

224
00:16:18,268 --> 00:16:20,770
[JAO] Kara, thanks for coming with me.

225
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:23,816
[JAO] I bought that ring because Allie deserves it.

226
00:16:24,358 --> 00:16:25,484
Have you seen Jao?

227
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:27,110
[QUINITO] I think he’s buying souvenirs.

228
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:29,529
[TANTAN] I saw him earlier.

229
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:31,073
He said he had somewhere to go.

230
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:33,449
[QUINITO] He’s flying back to Manila tomorrow, right?

231
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:35,369
[HAN BIN] Kara, you should go.

232
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:36,245
Want to walk around?

233
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:38,329
I really appreciate this, Kara,

234
00:16:38,330 --> 00:16:41,749
because I never get to talk about this with my friends in Manila.

235
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:45,838
[KARA] I believe everything happened for a reason.

236
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:47,464
Thanks, Kara.
